summary.text:
A blue moon contrary to its name and the image shown on the post, is not blue, its when a full moon happens twice in one month, which happens every 2.7 years. 

A super blue moon is when it's slightly brighter and appears 14% larger.

https://www.axios.com/2023/08/29/super-blue-moon-august-2023

“Hey, guys. As you can see, I am alive and well. My account was hacked. For the last 24 hours, I've been trying desperately to get into it. Somebody was playing a cruel joke and mocking my mental illness and the struggles I've gone through with depression and suicide attempts.”
